DURBAN - Five children died in two separate fires in Durban at the weekend.An eight-month-old baby and a five-year-old died in Phoenix when their house caught fire.READ: #CapeFires death toll continues to riseIn the Wyebank informal settlement, the bodies of six-year-old twins and a three-year-old were found burnt beyond recognition in their home.The causes of the fires are still unknown and circumstances surrounding the incidents are being investigated.eNCA